For t = 1,000 hours, β = 0.5, η = 1,000,000 hours:

F(1,000) = 1 - e^{-(1,000/1,000,000)^{0.5}} = 0.001292

The cumulative percent fallout = 0.001292 × 100% ≈ 0.13%.

